# PPDB AL-IMAM PROJECT RULES

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first, no config!)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth)
- React Hook Form + Zod

## Coding Style
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Use Bahasa Indonesia for comments
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Use Server Components by default
- Add "use client" only when needed

## Tailwind CSS v4 Rules
- No tailwind.config.js (CSS-first approach)
- All custom theme in globals.css @theme
- Use Islamic theme colors: brown, gold, teal, cream

## Component Structure
- Create reusable components in src/components
- Use Server Components when possible
- Client Components for interactivity only
- Proper TypeScript types from database.ts

## Database
- Use Supabase Client from @/lib/supabase/client
- Follow RLS policies
- Type-safe queries using database.ts types

## Best Practices
- Clean, readable code
- Proper error handling
- Loading states for async operations
- Responsive design (mobile-first)
- Accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- Islamic design principles (modest, professional)

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (StudentForm.tsx)
- Utils/Libs: camelCase (supabase.ts)
- Pages: lowercase-with-dashes

## Comments
- Use Bahasa Indonesia
- Explain WHY, not WHAT
